section.section:
To be covered under a health benefit plan offered by a carrier, a small employer shall:
elect to be covered;
agree to pay the premiums;
agree to offer coverage to any dependent of an eligible employee when coverage is sought by the eligible employee, in accordance with provisions governing late enrollees and any other provisions of this subtitle that apply to coverage;
agree to collect payments for premiums through payroll deductions for coverage of eligible employees and dependents and transmit those payments to the carrier; and
satisfy other reasonable provisions of the health benefit plan as approved by the Commissioner.
